        <briefdescription>
<para>Triggered state handler function for <ref refid="class_fw_info" kindref="compound">FwInfo</ref> events. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pElem</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to pointer to message of type <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns the state ID of the firmware download state</para>
</simplesect>
The function notify platform that command is accepted by calling function otaFwConfirm of the <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance. Pointer variable pd is assigned to <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance. Afterwards the message will be forwarded to firmware update task. Function start the download timeout timer by calling function startTimeout of the <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance. Finally function returns the state ID eDownload. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
